9. @RequestBody- Reading What the Client Sends
..............
When a client sends a POST or PUT request, 

JSON.
@RequestBody tells Spring to take that JSON and convert it into a Java object automatically.


/ Client sends this JSON:
// { "name": "Laptop", "price": 75000 }
@PostMapping("/products")
public ResponseEntity<Product> create(@RequestBody Product product) {
 // 'product' is already a Java object here
 // product.getName() → "Laptop"
 // product.getPrice() → 75000
 Product saved = productService.save(product);
